# Coding Style Rules for Bokat.se Project

1. Avoid nested if statements - use early returns instead
   - Check for error conditions first and return early
   - Use positive conditions for the main flow

2. Keep indentation levels minimal
   - Maximum of 2-3 levels of indentation per function
   - Extract complex logic into separate functions

3. Use guard clauses
   - Check for invalid conditions at the beginning of functions
   - Return early if preconditions are not met

4. Function structure
   - Functions should do one thing and do it well
   - Keep functions under 50 lines where possible
   - Extract reusable logic into helper functions

5. Variable naming
   - Use descriptive variable names
   - Prefix boolean variables with 'is_', 'has_', etc.
   - Use snake_case for variables and functions

6. Error handling
   - Log errors with appropriate level (debug, info, warning, error)
   - Include context in error messages
   - Return meaningful values on error (empty list, None, etc.)

7. Comments and documentation
   - Document function purpose, parameters, and return values
   - Add comments for complex logic
   - Keep comments up-to-date with code changes